MTN has introduced a new mobile price plan aimed at small and medium enterprises (SMEs). Made To Share gives up to 20 employees the ability to receive airtime and data bundles from a single, shareable wallet. The wallet can be managed by either the business owner or a designated administrator via the secure MyMTN App. Subscribers are given the option to choose from a variety of tariff plans that are customised to suit SMEs, usage and budget. Shareable data bundles range from 3GB to 700GB, while shareable airtime starts from 200 minutes of airtime, with the more extensive tariff plan offering 2,500 minutes per month. MTN said that the new plan offers the following benefits: The ability to add or remove additional users instantly;
The ability to set consumption limits and remotely monitor consumption in real time;
Free SMSes per day;
Free limited SIM cards;
Contracts are available on a month-to-month basis, or for a duration of 3, 6, 12 or 24 months. “Connectivity enables emerging businesses to compete with larger, more established companies in their industries,” said Wanda Matandela, chief enterprise officer at MTN Business. “Being the best network for business, MTN remains dedicated to introducing solutions that meet the ever-evolving needs of our customers and lead the delivery of a bold, new digital world.” You can read more about the offering here. Read: MTN may be forced to shut down hundreds of cell towers due to vandalism and theft 